  "claim_short": "2512.10442 Question 5.11 Hilbert-range subcase: if X is finite-dimensional and Y is uniformly convex, does (X,Y) have BPBp(-RSE)? Positive for Hilbert ranges: every operator X -> H has range in a Hilbert space of dimension at most dim X; finite-dimensional BPBp constants over H_1,...,H_dimX give BPBp, and source Corollary 2.8 upgrades to BPBp-RSE. Arbitrary uniformly convex ranges remain open in this attempt....",
